==Obtaining shards==
*Harvesting a [[crystal tree]] guarantees 8-10 shards per harvest, and can be increased to 14-16 if using [[ultracompost]].
*Completing [[The Gauntlet]].
*Defeating [[Zalcano]].
*Opening the [[Elven Crystal Chest]].
*Completing laps of the [[Prifddinas Agility Course]]. There is a 1/3 chance to receive a shard each time players travel through a shortcut portal.
*Catching [[crystal impling]]s gives a 1/18 chance of receiving 5-10 shards.
*Killing [[Guard (Prifddinas)|guards]] in Prifddinas and NPCs within the [[Iorwerth Dungeon]] gives a 1/24 chance of receiving a shard; [[superior slayer monster]]s are guaranteed to drop one.
*Pickpocketing an [[Elf (Thieving)|Elf]] inside of [[Prifddinas]] gives a 1/35 chance to receive a shard; wearing [[rogue equipment]] results in receiving two shards.
*Chopping any tree within [[Prifddinas]] with a 1/80 chance to receive crystal shard when receiving a log.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1229338862494920705|date=17 February 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.md/6O9NR|archivedate=19 February 2020|quote=1/80 if I'm reading this code correctly.|name=Prifddinas Trees Crystal Shard Droprate}} [[Gwenith]] does '''NOT''' count.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1250329003098918914|date=15 April 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.vn/qOyuX|archivedate=15 April 2020|quote=That area doesn't count as being in Prifddinas - I wouldn't expect one there at all.|name=Crystal shard tweet about woodcutting}}
*Mining ore in the [[Trahaearn mine]], mining [[tephra]] during the Zalcano fight, as well as mining a [[Crashed Star]], gives a 1/127 chance to obtain a crystal shard when mining an ore, regardless of type.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1250149976338038792|date=14 April 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.vn/c5H5d|archivedate=15 April 2019|quote=I believe that's 1/127 from any type of ore. And it looks like the Varrock bonus would give you a second shard roll if you got a second ore.|name=Crystal shard tweet about mining}}

If a player receives a shard along with a collected resource, while only having a single free inventory space, the crystal shard will be dropped to the floor instead.

===Exchanging seeds===
Players can also obtain crystal shards by exchanging various crystal seeds with [[Amrod]], who is found in the [[Hefin Inn]].

